# BACKEND ARCHITECTURE — PROGRESSIVE & SCALABLE

## PHILOSOPHY

> Do NOT apply everything at once. Read the complexity of what is being asked and apply the right level of architecture. Start simple, scale with purpose.

| Project Complexity | What to Apply |
|--------------------|---------------|
| **Small** — CRUD, few entities, simple rules | Clean Architecture + SOLID basics |
| **Medium** — business rules, multiple domains, integrations | + Value Objects, Result Pattern, Domain Events |
| **Large** — multiple bounded contexts, high traffic, team scale | + CQRS, Aggregates, Bounded Contexts, Sagas, Outbox |

**Never over-engineer.** If a simple use case works, don't add CQRS just because. Apply patterns when they solve a real problem.

---

## UNIVERSAL RULES (always apply)

1. **Dependencies point INWARD** — outer layers depend on inner layers, never the reverse
2. **The core is PURE** — no frameworks, no databases, no external libraries inside `core/`
3. **One use case = One action = One file**
4. **Un solo idioma para identificadores** — carpetas, archivos, variables, clases e interfaces: **inglés o español**, elegido **por proyecto** y aplicado **de forma consistente** (no mezclar en el mismo módulo sin decisión explícita). Los **comentarios** siguen la regla **modo Ask** (en este proyecto: español).
5. **Each class has one reason to change** (Single Responsibility)

---

## FOLDER STRUCTURE

```
src/
├── core/                          # INNER LAYER — pure business logic
│   ├── entities/                  # Business objects with rules
│   ├── value-objects/             # Immutable objects without identity (medium+)
│   ├── aggregates/                # Entity clusters with a root (large)
│   ├── use-cases/                 # One file per action
│   │   ├── commands/              # Write operations (medium+)
│   │   └── queries/               # Read operations (medium+)
│   ├── ports/                     # Contracts — define WHAT, not HOW
│   │   ├── repositories/
│   │   └── services/
│   └── events/                    # Domain Events (medium+)
│
├── adapters/                      # MIDDLE LAYER — connects core to outside
│   ├── controllers/
│   ├── repositories/
│   ├── event-handlers/            # Reacts to domain events (medium+)
│   └── external-services/
│
├── infrastructure/                # OUTER LAYER — framework, DB, config
│   ├── config/
│   ├── modules/
│   ├── bus/                       # Command/Query/Event bus (medium+)
│   └── database/
│       ├── schemas/
│       └── migrations/
│
└── shared/                        # Cross-cutting utilities
    ├── result/                    # Result Pattern (medium+)
    ├── exceptions/
    ├── validators/
    └── types/
```

