### LEVEL 3 — LARGE PROJECT

**Apply everything from Levels 1 and 2, plus:**
- CQRS (Commands and Queries separated)
- Aggregates
- Bounded Contexts
- Sagas / Process Managers

#### CQRS
> Separate write operations (Commands) from read operations (Queries).
> Queries never change state. Commands never return data (only confirmation).

```
// core/use-cases/commands/create-user.command.ts
// WRITES — has full business logic, validations, events

CLASS CreateUserCommand:
  INPUT: name, email
  OUTPUT: Result<{ id }>

  Does: validates, creates entity, saves, emits events

// core/use-cases/queries/get-user.query.ts
// READS — goes straight to data, no entity needed, no events

CLASS GetUserQuery:
  INPUT: userId
  OUTPUT: Result<UserDTO>

  Does: fetches directly from read model, maps to DTO, returns
```

> When to apply CQRS:
> ✅ Read and write loads are very different
> ✅ Queries need to join many tables or sources
> ✅ You have separate read/write databases
> ❌ Small project where reads and writes are equally simple

#### AGGREGATE
> A cluster of entities treated as a single unit.
> Only the root can be accessed from outside.
> All changes go through the root.

```
// core/aggregates/order.aggregate.ts

CLASS Order (Aggregate Root):
  PRIVATE id, items[], status, customerId

  METHOD addItem(product, quantity):
    IF status != PENDING → throw "Cannot modify confirmed order"
    item = new OrderItem(product, quantity)
    items.push(item)
    addDomainEvent(new ItemAddedToOrderEvent(...))

  METHOD confirm():
    IF items is empty → throw "Cannot confirm empty order"
    SET status = CONFIRMED
    addDomainEvent(new OrderConfirmedEvent(...))

// OrderItem is part of the aggregate but never accessed directly
// You always go through Order to change anything
```

#### BOUNDED CONTEXT
> Large system divided into independent domains.
> Each context has its own model, language, and team.
> They communicate through events, never direct imports.

```
Structure for a large system:

src/
├── contexts/
│   ├── users/          // Bounded Context: Users
│   │   ├── core/
│   │   ├── adapters/
│   │   └── infrastructure/
│   ├── orders/         // Bounded Context: Orders
│   │   ├── core/
│   │   ├── adapters/
│   │   └── infrastructure/
│   └── payments/       // Bounded Context: Payments
│       ├── core/
│       ├── adapters/
│       └── infrastructure/
```

> Rules between contexts:
> ✅ Communicate via Domain Events published to a bus
> ✅ Each context has its own User/Order/Product model — don't share entities
> ❌ Never import core/ from another context directly

#### SAGA / PROCESS MANAGER
> Coordinates a multi-step process that spans multiple contexts.
> Listens to events and decides what to do next.
> Handles failures and compensating actions.

```
// Example: Place Order Saga
// Coordinates: Orders → Payments → Inventory → Notifications

SAGA PlaceOrderSaga:

  ON OrderConfirmedEvent:
    → send ProcessPaymentCommand to Payments context

  ON PaymentSucceededEvent:
    → send ReserveInventoryCommand to Inventory context

  ON InventoryReservedEvent:
    → send SendConfirmationEmailCommand to Notifications context

  ON PaymentFailedEvent:
    → send CancelOrderCommand to Orders context  // compensating action

  ON InventoryUnavailableEvent:
    → send RefundPaymentCommand to Payments context  // compensating action
    → send CancelOrderCommand to Orders context
```

